valid_variations.reason: Modeling a variable-length byte string as a repeated group of single bytes is a common alternative to modeling it as an array field.

adjudication.reasoning: The UBX-LOG-STRING message is a simple container for 0-256 bytes of data. All extractions correctly identified the Class (0x21) and ID (0x04). The main discrepancy lies in whether the LLM modeled the variable payload as an array field ('fields' with 'array_of') or as a repeated group of single bytes ('repeated_groups'). Both are logically equivalent representations of the underlying binary protocol. Extraction 2 was marked as an error due to a non-standard JSON envelope wrapping the message data.
